16/01/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) plans to call an extraordinary session of Parliament regarding recent developments in neighbouring Iraq, primarily in Kirkuk and northern Iraq. 
AKP senior official Abdullatif Sener said on Monday (January 15th) that Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul would brief lawmakers during the session. 
Ankara claims bases of the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) are located in northern Iraq.
Also Monday, Turkish authorities reported that three PKK members were killed in separate clashes with Turkish security forces in the country's troubled southeast. 
(Sabah - 16/01/07; NTV - 15/01/07)
